        "@value": "Joint Action"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://placeholder.url#movementPattern",
    "@type": [
      "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty"
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment": [
      {
        "@value": "Use the most specific pattern that applies — prefer child patterns over parent patterns (e.g. Squat over KneeDominant, HorizontalPush over Push). Use a parent only when no child fits. Compound exercises may have more than one pattern. If no pattern fits well, return an empty array — do not force an ill-fitting label. Isolation exercises that are not curls, rows, presses, or hinges often have no clean pattern. Push and Pull patterns require multi-joint force production. Single-joint isolation movements (bicep curls, lateral raises, triceps extensions, leg extensions/curls) have no movement pattern — return empty array. Do not assign Pull to curls or Push to raises."
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain": [
      {
        "@id": "https://placeholder.url#Exercise"
      }
    ],
