        "@value": "Describes how limb involvement is distributed across the left and right sides of the body. Use feg:Bilateral for symmetric two-limb exercises. Use feg:Unilateral for exercises performed one limb at a time. Use feg:Contralateral when opposite limbs work together (e.g. bird dog, dead bug). Use feg:Ipsilateral when same-side limbs work together. Replaces the deprecated feg:isUnilateral boolean (ADR-075)."
